 <H1>Dependency Preserving Decompositions (Contd.)</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Decomposition of R into X and Y is dependency preserving if  (FX  union   FY ) +  =  F +
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>i.e., if we consider only dependencies in the closure F + that can be checked in X without considering Y, and in Y without considering X,  these imply all dependencies in F +.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Important to consider F +, not F, in this definition:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>ABC,  A      B,  B      C,  C      A, decomposed into AB and BC.
<LI>Is this dependency preserving?  Is  C       A  preserved?????
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Dependency preserving does not imply lossless join:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>ABC,  A       B,  decomposed into AB and BC.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>And vice-versa!  (Example?)</H2>
</UL></P>
